European Coal Derivatives Climb for a Second Consecutive Session

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-02-28T11:15:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/european-coal-derivatives-climb-for-a-second-consecutive-session.html
Benchmark European coal derivatives
had a second consecutive advance.  Coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or Antwerp with
settlement next year rose 25 cents, or 0.2 percent, to $121.75 a
metric ton at 11:01 a.m. in  London . Prices gained 0.8 percent on
Feb. 25.  The data are drawn from information supplied by ICAP Plc,
GFI Group Inc., Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Bloomberg, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter@bloomberg.net . 